      "content": "but isn't that just a way of saying that religious exemptions are basically just loopholes? it seems like whenever a law is passed to protect public health or civil rights, some groups just use religion as a way to ignore it. isn't it more of a problem for democracy when people can just pick and choose which laws apply to them based on their personal beliefs?",
